'''Wakae Shrine''' (わかえじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Gifu|Q45798|WD=Q45798|1=Gifu}}, {{ill|lt=Gifu Prefecture|Q131277|WD=Q131277|1=Gifu Prefecture}}. It is the Shikinaisha of {{ill|lt=Katagata District|Q11504366|WD=Q11504366|1=Katagata district}}, {{ill|lt=Mino Province|Q864156|WD=Q864156|1=Mino Province}}, listed in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}.

The {{ill|lt=Ilex rotunda|Q844306|WD=Q844306|1=Ilex rotunda}} and {{ill|lt=castanopsis|Q1065400|WD=Q1065400|1=Castanopsis}} trees in the precincts are designated preserved trees of Gifu City<ref>{{Cite web|和書|date=2010-03 |url=http://www.city.gifu.lg.jp/secure/7161/hozonnjyu21.3.pdf |title=保存樹・保存樹林一覧表 |format=PDF |publisher=岐阜市 |accessdate=2013-04-26}}</ref>.

=== Overview ===
*The founding period is unknown. It is said to have originally stood about 1 km west of the current site, and was relocated because of flooding.
*In the {{ill|lt=Edo period|Q184963|WD=Q184963|1=Edo period}}, it was called Wakamiya Hachimangū.
*When it was made a gōsha in {{ill|lt=1872|Q7753|WD=Q7753|1=1872}} (Meiji 5), it was renamed Wakae Shrine.
*The current shrine building was rebuilt in {{ill|lt=1916|Q2087|WD=Q2087|1=1916}} (Taishō 5).

=== Enshrined deities ===
*{{ill|lt=Emperor Ōjin|Q317997|WD=Q317997|lt=Emperor Ōjin|1=Emperor Ōjin}}
*{{ill|lt=Empress Jingū|Q232803|WD=Q232803|lt=Okinagatarashihime-no-Mikoto|1=Empress Jingū}}
*{{ill|lt=Tamayori-hime (Hyuga mythology)|Q3082751|WD=Q3082751|lt=Tamayori-hime-no-Mikoto|1=Tamayori-hime (mother of Jimmu)}}

=== Location ===
*1 Nishi-kaiden Higashi-kaiden Nyūaichi Aza Kaibuchi, Gifu, Gifu Prefecture

=== Transportation ===
{{ill|lt=Gifu Bus|Q5560101|WD=Q5560101|lt=Gifu Bus|1=Gifu Bus}}
*Get off at "Nishi-kaiden" on the Saigō Line, 8 minutes on foot
*Get off at "Matsunoki" on the Sogaya Line, 5 minutes on foot

